# Dual Cursor / Parallel Projects (Mandatory — PIPBONG Window)

**Status:** Policy added 2026-07 (v0.8.224). PIPBONG and another project may run in **separate Cursor windows** with simultaneous incremental builds when these rules hold.

## One-time setup (PIPBONG window)

```powershell
.\scripts\ensure-dev-isolation.ps1
```

Then **Developer: Reload Window**.

## Required invariants (this repo)

| Item | Rule |
|------|------|
| Window | **File → Open Folder** → `PIPBONG` only — not multi-root with another project |
| Build | `.\scripts\build-release.ps1` / Ctrl+Shift+B — **never** CMake Tools configure |
| F5 | `config.pipbong.f5BuildAndRun` in `.vscode/settings.json`; `fix-pipbong-cursor-f5.ps1` gates F5 to this workspace only |
| vcpkg lock | `build-common.ps1` **waits** — does **not** kill global cmake/vcpkg during normal builds |
| Recovery | `recover-ide-build.ps1` local by default; `-KillGlobalBuildProcesses` only when alone |
| Qt | `build-and-run.ps1` auto-runs `deploy-qt.ps1` when `platforms/qwindows.dll` missing |
| Cache path | `Test-CMakeCachePathMismatch` clears `build/` on folder rename |

## Anti-patterns

| Do not | Why |
|--------|-----|
| `recover-ide-build.ps1 -KillGlobalBuildProcesses` while other window builds | Kills their cmake/vcpkg/msbuild |
| CMake Tools **[Configure]** in either window during parallel work | vcpkg manifest contention |
| Share one `build/` folder between repos | CMake cache corruption |
| Unconditional global F5 → tasks.test | Breaks other project's debug F5 |

